<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Zephyr merge list</title>

<style>
/* Theme: every color lives in a variable so light and dark stay in sync. */
:root {
	--bg: #f6f7f9;
	--panel: #ffffff;
	--fg: #1d2531;
	--muted: #5d6b83;
	--border: #dce2eb;
	--accent: #6e37c8;
	--ok: #1a7f37;
	--ok-bg: #def0e3;
	--warn: #7d5c00;
	--warn-bg: #fdeeba;
	--bad: #b42323;
	--bad-bg: #fbe2e2;
	--neutral-bg: #e8ecf2;
	--row-ready: #effaf1;
	--row-hover: #eef1f6;
	--header-bg: #333f67;
	--header-fg: #ffffff;
}
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
	:root {
		--bg: #0e1116;
		--panel: #171c24;
		--fg: #e3e7ee;
		--muted: #98a4b8;
		--border: #2c3442;
		--accent: #a97ff0;
		--ok: #4ecb71;
		--ok-bg: #17311d;
		--warn: #e8c341;
		--warn-bg: #37300e;
		--bad: #f47070;
		--bad-bg: #3d1a1a;
		--neutral-bg: #232a36;
		--row-ready: #14231a;
		--row-hover: #202836;
		--header-bg: #232c4a;
		--header-fg: #dfe4f2;
	}
}

* { box-sizing: border-box; }

body {
	margin: 0 auto;
	padding: 16px 24px 32px;
	max-width: 1600px;
	background: var(--bg);
	color: var(--fg);
	font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
	font-size: 14px;
	line-height: 1.45;
}

a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

/* ---- Page header ------------------------------------------------------ */

.page-header { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.page-header h1 { margin: 8px 0 0; font-size: 24px; }
.page-header .subtitle { color: var(--muted); margin: 0; }

/* ---- Summary cards ----------------------------------------------------- */

.summary {
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
	gap: 12px;
	margin: 16px 0;
}

.card {
	background: var(--panel);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: 8px;
	padding: 10px 14px;
}

.card .card-label {
	font-size: 11px;
	font-weight: 600;
	letter-spacing: 0.06em;
	text-transform: uppercase;
	color: var(--muted);
	margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.card .card-value { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; }
.card .card-note { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); }
.card .big { font-size: 24px; color: var(--ok); }

.ci-badges { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; }

.ci-badge {
	display: inline-block;
	padding: 1px 8px;
	border-radius: 999px;
	font-size: 12px;
	background: var(--neutral-bg);
	white-space: nowrap;
}
.ci-badge::before { margin-right: 4px; }
.ci-pass { background: var(--ok-bg); color: var(--ok); }
.ci-pass::before { content: "\2713"; }
.ci-fail { background: var(--bad-bg); color: var(--bad); }
.ci-fail::before { content: "\2715"; }
.ci-cancelled { background: var(--warn-bg); color: var(--warn); }
.ci-cancelled::before { content: "\2298"; }
.ci-running { background: var(--neutral-bg); color: var(--muted); }
.ci-running::before { content: "\27F3"; }

/* ---- MOTD banner ------------------------------------------------------- */

.motd {
	border: 1px solid var(--bad);
	border-left-width: 6px;
	border-radius: 8px;
	background: var(--bad-bg);
	padding: 10px 14px;
	margin: 12px 0;
}

/* ---- Filter controls ---------------------------------------------------- */

.controls {
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	gap: 12px;
	flex-wrap: wrap;
	margin: 12px 0;
}

#pr-search {
	padding: 6px 12px;
	min-width: 280px;
	background: var(--panel);
	color: var(--fg);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: 6px;
	font-size: 13px;
}
#pr-search:focus { outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: -1px; }

.chips { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; }

.chip {
	padding: 4px 12px;
	background: var(--panel);
	color: var(--muted);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: 999px;
	font-size: 13px;
	font-weight: 600;
	cursor: pointer;
}
.chip:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
.chip.active {
	background: var(--accent);
	border-color: var(--accent);
	color: var(--bg);
}
.chip .count { font-weight: 400; opacity: 0.8; }

/* ---- Table ------------------------------------------------------------- */

.table-wrap {
	background: var(--panel);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: 8px;
	overflow-x: auto;
}

.prs { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; }

.prs th, .prs td {
	padding: 6px 10px;
	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
	text-align: left;
	vertical-align: top;
}

.prs thead th {
	position: sticky;
	top: 0;
	background: var(--header-bg);
	color: var(--header-fg);
	font-size: 12px;
	white-space: nowrap;
	cursor: help;
}

/* Sortable columns: pointer cursor plus an arrow when a sort is active. */
.prs thead th.sortable { cursor: pointer; user-select: none; }
.prs thead th.sortable[aria-sort="ascending"]::after { content: " \25B4"; }
.prs thead th.sortable[aria-sort="descending"]::after { content: " \25BE"; }

.prs tfoot td { color: var(--muted); text-align: center; padding: 16px; }

.prs tbody tr:hover { background: var(--row-hover); }
.prs tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }

.prs tr.status-ready { background: var(--row-ready); }
.prs tr.status-ready:hover { background: var(--row-hover); }

.prs td.num, .prs td.gate { white-space: nowrap; }
.prs td.gate { text-align: center; }
.prs th.gate-col { text-align: center; }

.gate-pass { color: var(--ok); font-weight: 600; }
.gate-fail { color: var(--bad); font-weight: 600; }
.gate-wait { color: var(--warn); font-weight: 600; white-space: nowrap; }
.gate-unknown { color: var(--muted); }

.muted { color: var(--muted); }

/* ---- Status pills ------------------------------------------------------ */

.pill {
	display: inline-block;
	padding: 1px 9px;
	border-radius: 999px;
	font-size: 12px;
	font-weight: 600;
	white-space: nowrap;
	cursor: default;
}
.pill-ready { background: var(--ok-bg); color: var(--ok); }
.pill-waiting { background: var(--warn-bg); color: var(--warn); }
.pill-blocked { background: var(--bad-bg); color: var(--bad); }
.pill-unknown { background: var(--neutral-bg); color: var(--muted); }

/* ---- Label tags (shown next to PR titles) ------------------------------ */

.tag {
	display: inline-block;
	padding: 0 6px;
	border-radius: 4px;
	font-size: 11px;
	font-weight: 600;
	white-space: nowrap;
	cursor: default;
}
.tag-hotfix { background: #b60205; color: white; }
.tag-trivial { background: #f9d0b1; color: #402000; }
.tag-override { background: #6f42c1; color: white; }
.tag-oldci { background: #fef2c0; color: #574b00; }
.tag-dismissed { background: #ff69b4; color: #3d0d24; }
.tag-dnm { background: #b60205; color: white; }

/* ---- Footer / misc ----------------------------------------------------- */

.toolbar {
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	gap: 16px;
	flex-wrap: wrap;
	margin: 12px 0;
}

.open-ready-button {
	padding: 6px 14px;
	background: var(--ok);
	color: var(--bg);
	border: none;
	border-radius: 6px;
	font-size: 13px;
	font-weight: 600;
	cursor: pointer;
}
.open-ready-button:hover { filter: brightness(1.15); }

.help { margin: 16px 0; color: var(--fg); max-width: 900px; }
.help summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; color: var(--muted); }
.help h4 { margin: 12px 0 4px; }
.help td, .help th { padding: 2px 10px 2px 0; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }

footer { margin-top: 20px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; }
footer img { vertical-align: middle; }
</style>

<script>
"use strict";

/* Message of the day: maintained on the Zephyr wiki, shown when not "empty". */
function loadMotd() {
	const url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wiki/zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr/Merge-List-MOTD.md";
	fetch(url)
		.then((response) => {
			if (!response.ok) {
				throw new Error("HTTP error: " + response.status);
			}
			return response.text();
		})
		.then((text) => {
			if (text.trim() == "empty") {
				return;
			}
			const banner = document.getElementById("motd");
			banner.textContent = text;
			banner.hidden = false;
		})
		.catch((error) => console.log("motd: " + error));
}

/* Show "12 minutes ago" instead of a raw ISO timestamp. */
function renderUpdateTime() {
	const el = document.getElementById("update-timestamp");
	const then = Date.parse(el.getAttribute("datetime"));
	const seconds = Math.round((then - Date.now()) / 1000);
	const rtf = new Intl.RelativeTimeFormat(undefined, { numeric: "auto" });

	let text;
	if (Math.abs(seconds) < 60) {
		text = rtf.format(seconds, "second");
	} else if (Math.abs(seconds) < 3600) {
		text = rtf.format(Math.round(seconds / 60), "minute");
	} else if (Math.abs(seconds) < 86400) {
		text = rtf.format(Math.round(seconds / 3600), "hour");
	} else {
		text = rtf.format(Math.round(seconds / 86400), "day");
	}
	el.textContent = text;
	el.title = new Date(then).toString();
}

/* Auto-refresh: opt-in via checkbox, remembered in localStorage. */
function setupAutoRefresh() {
	const checkbox = document.getElementById("auto-refresh");
	checkbox.checked = localStorage.getItem("autoRefresh") == "true";
	checkbox.addEventListener("change", () => {
		localStorage.setItem("autoRefresh", checkbox.checked);
	});
	setInterval(() => {
		if (checkbox.checked) {
			location.reload();
		}
	}, 60000);
}

/* Open every PR that is ready to merge into main, each in its own tab. */
function openReadyPRs() {
	const rows = document.querySelectorAll(
		'#pr-table tr[data-status="ready"][data-base="main"]');

	if (rows.length == 0) {
		alert("No PRs are ready to merge into main right now.");
		return;
	}
	rows.forEach((row) => {
		const link = row.querySelector("a");
		if (link) {
			window.open(link.href, "_blank");
		}
	});
}

/* Text search plus status chips; a row must match both to stay visible. */
function setupFilters() {
	const search = document.getElementById("pr-search");
	const chips = document.querySelectorAll("#status-chips .chip");
	const rows = document.querySelectorAll("#pr-table tbody tr");
	const noMatch = document.getElementById("no-match");

	chips.forEach((chip) => {
		const status = chip.dataset.status;
		const count = status
			? document.querySelectorAll(`#pr-table tbody tr[data-status="${status}"]`).length
			: rows.length;
		chip.insertAdjacentHTML("beforeend", ` <span class="count">${count}</span>`);
	});

	function apply() {
		const text = search.value.trim().toLowerCase();
		const status = document.querySelector("#status-chips .active").dataset.status;

		let shown = 0;
		rows.forEach((row) => {
			const match =
				(!status || row.dataset.status == status) &&
				(!text || row.textContent.toLowerCase().includes(text));
			row.hidden = !match;
			shown += match;
		});
		noMatch.hidden = shown > 0;
	}

	search.addEventListener("input", apply);
	chips.forEach((chip) => {
		chip.addEventListener("click", () => {
			chips.forEach((c) => c.classList.remove("active"));
			chip.classList.add("active");
			apply();
		});
	});
}

/* Click a column header to sort; click again to reverse. */
function setupSorting() {
	const table = document.getElementById("pr-table");
	const statusRank = { ready: 0, waiting: 1, unknown: 2, blocked: 3 };

	function sortValue(row, column, kind) {
		if (kind == "status") {
			// Rank by status, then by hours left within "waiting".
			const hours = parseFloat(row.querySelector(".pill").textContent) || 0;
			return statusRank[row.dataset.status] * 10000 + hours;
		}
		const text = row.cells[column].textContent.trim();
		return kind == "number" ? parseInt(text, 10) : text.toLowerCase();
	}

	table.querySelectorAll("th.sortable").forEach((th) => {
		th.addEventListener("click", () => {
			const ascending = th.getAttribute("aria-sort") != "ascending";
			table.querySelectorAll("th.sortable").forEach(
				(other) => other.removeAttribute("aria-sort"));
			th.setAttribute("aria-sort", ascending ? "ascending" : "descending");

			const tbody = table.tBodies[0];
			const column = th.cellIndex;
			const kind = th.dataset.sort;
			Array.from(tbody.rows)
				.map((row) => [sortValue(row, column, kind), row])
				.sort(([a], [b]) => {
					const cmp = a < b ? -1 : a > b ? 1 : 0;
					return ascending ? cmp : -cmp;
				})
				.forEach(([, row]) => tbody.appendChild(row));
		});
	});
}

addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
	loadMotd();
	renderUpdateTime();
	setInterval(renderUpdateTime, 30000);
	setupAutoRefresh();
	setupFilters();
	setupSorting();
});
</script>

</head>

<body>

<div class="page-header">
	<h1>Zephyr merge list</h1>
	<p class="subtitle">Open pull requests that are approved, pass CI, and are
	in line to be merged into
	<a href="https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr">zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr</a>.</p>
</div>

<div class="motd" id="motd" role="alert" hidden></div>

<div class="summary">
	<div class="card">
		<div class="card-label">Ready to merge</div>
		<div class="card-value"><span class="big">READY_COUNT</span> of TOTAL_COUNT listed</div>
		<div class="card-note">PRs that pass all three merge gates</div>
	</div>
	<div class="card">
		<div class="card-label">CI on main</div>
		<div class="ci-badges">CI_STATUS</div>
	</div>
	<div class="card">
		<div class="card-label">Release phase</div>
		<div class="card-value" title="RELEASE_PHASE_HINT">RELEASE_PHASE</div>
		<div class="card-note">RELEASE_PHASE_DETAIL</div>
	</div>
	<div class="card">
		<div class="card-label">Last updated</div>
		<div class="card-value">
			<time id="update-timestamp" datetime="UPDATE_TIMESTAMP">UPDATE_TIMESTAMP</time>
		</div>
		<div class="card-note">
			<label><input type="checkbox" id="auto-refresh"> refresh automatically</label>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="controls">
	<input type="search" id="pr-search"
		placeholder="Filter by number, title, author, branch&hellip;"
		aria-label="Filter pull requests">
	<div class="chips" id="status-chips" role="group" aria-label="Filter by status">
		<button class="chip active" data-status="">All</button>
		<button class="chip" data-status="ready">Ready</button>
		<button class="chip" data-status="waiting">Waiting</button>
		<button class="chip" data-status="blocked">Blocked</button>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="table-wrap">
<table class="prs" id="pr-table">
	<thead>
	<tr>
		<th class="sortable" data-sort="number" title="Pull request number (click to sort)">PR</th>
		<th class="sortable" data-sort="text" title="Pull request title and labels (click to sort)">Title</th>
		<th class="sortable" data-sort="status" title="Summary: is this PR ready to merge, and if not, why not? (click to sort)">Status</th>
		<th class="gate-col" title="Gate 1: the PR applies cleanly on its target branch (no merge conflicts)">Conflict&#8209;free</th>
		<th class="gate-col" title="Gate 2: an assignee approved the PR (auto-passes for hotfixes, unassigned PRs, or when the author is the assignee)">Assignee approval</th>
		<th class="gate-col" title="Gate 3: the minimum review window has elapsed &mdash; 48 business hours, 4 hours for trivial PRs, none for hotfixes">Review time</th>
		<th class="sortable" data-sort="text" title="Who opened the PR (click to sort)">Author</th>
		<th class="sortable" data-sort="text" title="Maintainers assigned to shepherd the PR (click to sort)">Assignees</th>
		<th class="sortable" data-sort="text" title="Reviewers whose approval currently stands (click to sort)">Approvers</th>
		<th class="sortable" data-sort="text" title="Branch the PR will be merged into, plus its milestone if set (click to sort)">Target</th>
	</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
<!-- PR_ROWS -->
	</tbody>
	<tfoot>
	<tr id="no-match" hidden><td colspan="10">No pull requests match the current filter.</td></tr>
	</tfoot>
</table>
</div>

<div class="toolbar">
	<button onclick="openReadyPRs()" class="open-ready-button">Open all ready PRs &nearr;</button>
</div>

<details class="help">
	<summary>How this list works</summary>

	<h4>Which PRs show up here?</h4>
	<p>A pull request appears once it is open, not a draft, approved by
	reviewers, and passing CI. In other words: everything here is already
	through code review &mdash; this page tracks the final wait before a release
	engineer merges it.</p>

	<h4>The three merge gates</h4>
	<p>A PR is merged when all three gates pass:</p>
	<ol>
		<li><b>Conflict-free</b> &mdash; it applies cleanly on its target branch.
		If not, the author needs to rebase.</li>
		<li><b>Assignee approval</b> &mdash; the assigned maintainer approved it.
		This gate passes automatically for hotfixes, for PRs with no assignee,
		and when the author is the assignee.</li>
		<li><b>Review time</b> &mdash; a minimum review window since the PR became
		ready for review, so that everyone has a fair chance to comment:
		48 business hours normally, 4 hours for <i>trivial</i> PRs, none for
		<i>hotfixes</i>.</li>
	</ol>
	<p>The <b>Status</b> column sums this up: <span class="pill pill-ready">Ready</span>
	means all gates pass and the PR will be picked up in the next merge round;
	<span class="pill pill-waiting">12h left</span> means it is only waiting for
	the review window to elapse; <span class="pill pill-blocked">Merge conflict</span>
	or <span class="pill pill-blocked">Needs assignee</span> means the author or
	assignee has to act first.</p>

	<h4>Labels</h4>
	<table>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-hotfix">hotfix</span></td>
			<td>Fixes a broken main branch; merged immediately.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-trivial">trivial</span></td>
			<td>Small, low-risk change; the review window is 4 hours instead of 48 business hours.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-override">override required</span></td>
			<td>A release engineer must override a failing or stuck required check to merge.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-oldci">ci 42d</span></td>
			<td>The last full CI run is that many days old; CI should be re-run before merging.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-dismissed">review dismissed</span></td>
			<td>A &ldquo;changes requested&rdquo; review was dismissed by someone else; merits a second look.</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="tag tag-dnm">dnm</span></td>
			<td>Do not merge.</td></tr>
	</table>

	<h4>Release phase</h4>
	<p>During <b>integration</b>, features and fixes merge normally. After the
	feature freeze milestone, the project is in <b>feature freeze</b>: only bug
	fixes and release-blocking work are merged until the release is tagged, and
	PRs milestoned for the next release wait.</p>
</details>

<footer>
	<a href="https://github.com/REPOSITORY_PATH/actions/workflows/update.yaml">
		<img src="https://github.com/REPOSITORY_PATH/actions/workflows/update.yaml/badge.svg" alt="update workflow status">
	</a>
	&mdash; generated by <a href="https://github.com/REPOSITORY_PATH">REPOSITORY_PATH</a>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
